Q3 closed — keep simple, acknowledge two zones, rename Bottle → Crucible Orchestration, review during Pace 3.

## Q4 — Significant Events → RBSPH

New file `Tools/rbk/vov_veiled/RBSPH-ProjectHistory.adoc`. Move the entire Significant Events table out of RBSCO, verbatim. Preserve the AsciiDoc table format (terser than bullets for date-driven content), preserve commented-out entries.

Header comment proposal:

```
// RBSPH-ProjectHistory.adoc
//
// Recipe Bottle Project History — significant events timeline
//
// PURPOSE: Internal project memory. Each entry captures a structural
// turning point: infrastructure migrations, failed approaches, newly
// established concepts. Terse by design — dates, one-line events, no
// narrative wrapping. Commented-out entries are historical notes
// preserved for possible reactivation.
//
// ANCESTRY: Extracted from RBSCO-CosmologyIntro.adoc during ₣A5
// (rbk-mvp-3-public-docs-refresh).
//
// DEPENDENCY: Requires RBS0-SpecTop.adoc mapping section for
// attribute resolution (entries cite {at_*}, {st_*} attributes).
```

RBSCO gains one cross-reference line replacing the old table: `See \`RBSPH-ProjectHistory.adoc\` for the project's significant events timeline.`

Good?
